The Federal Government has appointed Dr Peter Okwudilichukwu Ogbobe as the Director-General of the Projects Development Institute (PRODA), Enugu. Ogbobe’s appointment is contained in a letter dated May 20, 2022, and signed by Prof Ibrahim Gambari, the Chief of Staff to the President. PRP issues certificates of return to Abiola, 21 gov’ship candidates Running mate: I believe in politics of inclusion – Lalong According to the statement by PRODA yesterday, the appointment of Ogbobe takes effect immediately and is a non-renewable five-year tenure. Until his appointment, Ogbobe was the Director, Information and Communication Technology (ICT) at the National Board for Technology Incubation (NBTI). Ogbobe is a member: Council for the Regulation of Engineering in Nigeria (COREN), Nigeria Society of Engineers (NSE), American Society of Mechanical Engineers (ASME), among other 